s) || 2 || \n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small|Wins the [[World Kickboxing Association|WKA]] European Super Heavyweight (+95 kg/209 lb) Championship.}}\n|-\n|}</div></div>\n'''''Legend''''': {{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win |border=1px solid #CCFFCC}}\n{{legend2|#FFBBBB|Loss |border=1px solid #FFBBBB}}\n{{legend2|#c5d2ea|Draw/No contest |border=1px solid #c5d2ea}}\n{{legend2|White|Notes |border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kabashi, Besim}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:2011 deaths]]\n[[Category:German male kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Light heavyweight kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Cruiserweight kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Heavyweight kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Albanian Muay Thai practitioners]]\n[[Category:German Muay Thai practitioners]]\n[[Category:People from Istok]]\n[[Category:People from Munich]]\n[[Category:Kosovo Albanians]]\n[[Category:German people of Albanian descent]]\n[[Category:German people of Kosovan descent]]\n[[Category:Kosovan emigrants to Germany]]\n[[Category:Drug-related deaths in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses2|Kabashi}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Besim Kabashi\n| native_name     = \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| caption         =  \n| birth_name      = \n| other_names     = \n| nationality     = {{Flag icon|Kosovo}} [[Kosovo]] \n| birth_date      = {{birth date|1976|2|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place     = [[Istok]], [[Socialist Autonomous Province of Kosovo|SAP Kosovo]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| fighting_out_of = [[Munich]], [[Germany]]\n| death_date      = {{death date and age|2011|12|4|1976|2|27|df=yes}}\n| death_place     = [[Munich]], [[Germany]]\n| height          = {{height|m=1.87|precision=1}}\n| weight          = {{convert|102|kg|lb st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Light Heavyweight]] <br> [[Cruiserweight (kickboxing)|Cruiserweight]] <br> [[Heavyweight]]\n| style           = [[Kickboxing]]{{*}}[[Muay Thai]]\n| rank            = \n| stance          = Muslim\n| team            = KS Steko\n| trainer         = \n| years_active    = 1997\u20132002 <br> 2006\u20132011\n| kickbox_win     = 65\n| kickbox_kowin   = 60\n| kickbox_loss    = 1\n| kickbox_koloss  = \n| kickbox_draw    = 0\n| kickbox_nc      = \n| other           = \n| occupation      = \n| spouse          = \n| children        = \n| relatives       = \n| students        = \n| university      =\n| url             = \n| updated         = \n}}\n\n'''Besim Kabashi''' (February 27, 1976 \u2013 December 4, 2011) was a Kosovar-German [[Kickboxing|kickboxer]] who competed in the [[light heavyweight]], [[cruiserweight]] and [[heavyweight]] divisions. He began his training in Germany after emigrating from [[Kosovo]] and initially competed as a -79&nbsp;kg/174&nbsp;lb fighter before moving up through the weight classes until eventually reaching heavyweight. After stints as a German and European champion, Kabashi won the [[World Kickboxing Association|WKA]] World Heavyweight Muay Thai title in 2008. Although he defended this belt numerous times and had an impressive 80% [[knockout]] ratio, he rarely fought outside him hometown of [[Munich]] or against top-ranked competition, and so was never considered elite at any weight class.<ref>[http://www.thmnews.com/wka-world-champion-besim-kabashi-tiger-muay-thai-training-highlight-reel.html Besim Kabashi]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe died from a heart attack in December 2011.\n\n==Early life==\nKabashi was born as the youngest of seven children to [[Kosovar Albanian]] parents near [[Istok]], [[Yugoslavia]] in 1976 and moved to Munich, Germany at the age of fourteen. He competed in athletics, football and swimming as a youngster before he began kickboxing when he was seventeen.<ref>[http://www.albanianboxing.com/legjendat/besim-kabashi.html Biografia e kikboksierit Besim Kabashi] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010222034/http://www.albanianboxing.com/legjendat/besim-kabashi.html |date=October 10, 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter successful careers in amateur boxing and kickboxing, Kabashi turned professional in 1997 and won the [[World Kickboxing Association|WKA]] German Light Heavyweight (-79&nbsp;kg/174&nbsp;lb) Championship in his debut year. He then followed this up by taking the WKA German Super Light Heavyweight (-83.2&nbsp;kg/183&nbsp;lb) title the following year. Despite a promising start to his career, Kabashi would then retire from the sport in 2002 following a disagreement with his trainer.\n\nHe returned to the ring in 2006, weighing in at 102&nbsp;kg/224&nbsp;lb. His transition to heavyweight saw him have success almost immediately as he [[Knockout|knocked out]] Zoran Dorcic in round two to become the WKA European Super Heavyweight (+95&nbsp;kg/209&nbsp;lb) Champion in 2007. He then won the WKA World Heavyweight (-95&nbsp;kg/209&nbsp;lb) Muay Thai belt on December 13, 2008 when he defeated Yahya G\u00fclay by fourth round [[technical knockout]]. Kabashi defended this title seven times over the next three years against the likes of [[David Dancrade]] and [[Petr Vondr\u00e1\u010dek]] before his untimely death in December 2011.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.telajmi.com/lajmi/6888/besim-kabashi-mposht-petr-vondracek-me-ko-n-raundin-4.html |title=Besim Kabashi mposht Petr Vondracek me KO n\u00eb raundin 4 |access-date=2012-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126011613/http://www.telajmi.com/lajmi/6888/besim-kabashi-mposht-petr-vondracek-me-ko-n-raundin-4.html |archive-date=2013-01-26 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nKabashi was found dead in his apartment in Munich, Germany on Sunday December 4, 2011.<ref>\n{{cite web\n|url=http://www.bild.de/regional/muenchen/muenchen/der-seltsame-tod-des-thai-boxers-kabashi-21413824.bild.html\n|title=Der seltsame Tod des Thai-Boxers\n|language=German\n|publisher=[[Bild]]\n|date= 2011-12-06\n|accessdate=2012-02-19\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/Toter-Kickboxer-Raetsel-um-angeblichen-Abschiedsbrief-id17937481.html\n|title=Toter Kickboxer: R\u00e4tsel um angeblichen Abschiedsbrief\n|language=German\n|publisher=[[Augsburger Allgemeine]]\n|date=2011-12-15\n|accessdate=2012-02-19\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213135647/http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/Toter-Kickboxer-Raetsel-um-angeblichen-Abschiedsbrief-id17937481.html\n|archive-date=2012-02-13\n|url-status=live\n}}</ref>\n\n==Championships and awards==\n\n===Kickboxing===\n*'''[[World Kickboxing Association]]'''\n**WKA German Light Heavyweight (-79&nbsp;kg/174&nbsp;lb) Championship\n**WKA German Super Light Heavyweight (-83.2&nbsp;kg/183&nbsp;lb) Championship\n**WKA European Super Heavyweight (+95&nbsp;kg/209&nbsp;lb) Championship\n**WKA World Heavyweight (-95&nbsp;kg/209&nbsp;lb) Muay Thai Championship\n\n== Kickboxing record ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" width=100% style=\"clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; font-size:85%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"background:#A9A9A9\" | <span style=\"color:white;\">Kickboxing record</span>\n|- valign=\"top\" \n|<div class=\"NavFrame\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"background:white; \"><span style=\"color:black;\">'''65 wins''' (60 KOs), '''1 loss''', '''0 draws'''</span></div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:left; display:collapse;\">\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#dddddd\"\n| '''Date''' || '''Result''' || '''Opponent''' || '''Event''' || '''Location''' || '''Method''' || '''Round''' || '''Time'''\n|-\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFCC\"\n| 2011-05-28 || Win ||align=left|{{flagicon|CZE}} [[Petr Vondr\u00e1\u010dek]] || Steko's Fight Night || [[Munich, Germany]] || TKO (punches) || 4 || 1:27\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small|Retains the [[World Kickboxing Association|WKA]] World Heavyweight (-95 kg/209 lb) Muay Thai Championship.}}\n|